The funeral service for stalwart and ambassador John Nkadimeng is underway at his home in Kew, North of Johannesburg. A family Pastor, Deacon Mathe is leading the prayer. The video below is an update from the funeral:  President Cyril Ramaphosa is expected to deliver the eulogy at the main service at Marks Park Sports Club in Johannesburg. Dignitaries such as Minister in the Presidency, Jackson Mthembu, ANC Secretary General, Ace Magashule and SACP’s Solly Mapaila are in attendance. At the end of the service, Magashule will hand over the party flag to the family as a symbol of gratitude for Nkadimeng’s service to the ANC. The video below is the live stream of the funeral service:  